.TH "sk_ns_capable" 9 "sk_ns_capable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sk_ns_capable \- General socket capability test
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" sk_ns_capable
.BI "(const struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "struct user_namespace *user_ns "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
Socket to use a capability on or through
.IP "user_ns" 12
The user namespace of the capability to use
.IP "cap" 12
The capability to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Test to see if the opener of the socket had when the socket was
created and the current process has the capability \fIcap\fP in the user
namespace \fIuser_ns\fP.
